title: german potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, slice or cut into 1/2-inch pieces and boil in salted water just until tender.
(Be careful not to overcook or the potatoes will become mush.)
Meanwhile cut bacon into small pieces. Cut onion into small pieces or green onions into thin slices.
Mix together vinegar, water, sugar, pepper and salt.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp, then scoop bacon out of skillet into vinegar mixture, leaving drippings in skillet.
Saute onion in drippings. Add flour to onion in skillet and stir until smooth and thickened. Drain potatoes (when tender) and pour into skillet.
Add bacon/vinegar mixture and stir gently to mix evenly.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix all ingredients except pecans.
Stir thoroughly and cook to 238°.
Stir often.
Cool to 170° and add pecans.
Stir until thick.
Pour onto a buttered platter and cut into squares.

title: fish chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; mix in celery and onion.
Arrange fish fillets on top.
Cover and simmer until fish is done, about 20 minutes for frozen fish, 10 minutes for fresh.
Break up the fish with a spoon into bite size chunks.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer gently for 30 minutes.

title: grilled red potatoes
directions: Slice garlic cloves.
Mix with olive oil.
Set aside for at least 4 hours.
Wash potatoes.
Cut into quarters.
Place into microwavesafe covered dish.
Add water.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes on High in microwave or until tender.
Drain water.
Place on grill; brush with olive oil mix.
Turn occasionally until slightly crisp. Serve immediately.

title: skillet herbed chicken
directions: Loosen skin of chicken with fingers, working from breast side. Cut off wing tips.
Blend butter with lemon peels, salt and herbs. Spread on the meat under the skin and skewer wing to breast. Heat a 9-inch skillet over moderate heat and place chicken, skin side down, in
the dry pan.
Cover and cook over medium heat 25 minutes or until chicken is nicely browned and tender.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Combine bran flakes, milk and carrots; let stand 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, stirring until particles are moistened. Line each muffin tin with two paper liners; fill half full.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries and oranges, including rind, through grinder. Add celery, nuts and sugar.
Make Jell-O using only 1 1/2 cups water.
Add other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until thick. Serve with whip cream.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Beat together cream cheese and margarine.
Mix pudding and milk.
Blend the two mixtures.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer cookies and pudding mixture in a bowl.
(For children's parties, fill clear, plastic cups and garnish with gummy worms.)
Refrigerate for one hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Slowly cook meat, onion, celery and bell pepper until celery and onion are tender.
Add uncooked rice and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat until thickened.
Add to beaten egg yolks.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken and remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring.
Pour this over banana and vanilla wafers which have been layered.
Top with meringue and brown lightly.

title: beef brisket pot roast
directions: Heat large heavy pot.
Add meat.
Brown on all sides without oil.
Pour off any fat.
Sprinkle onion around meat.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Keep covered and let meat cool to lukewarm.
When cool, slice across grain for serving.
Return meat to pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours longer or until tender, turning slices once.

title: sweet pickle recipe
directions: Put cucumbers in stone	jar or glass.
Pour over them 1 gallon boiling water with	1 teacup salt dissolved.
Let stand 8 days. On the 8th	day,
drain off water and wash good. Then pour	over gallon boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Ninth day,
pour over
a
gallon
boiling
water
with 1 tablespoon powdered
alum; let stand 24 hours.
Tenth day, drain and pour over
1 gallon boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Eleventh day, drain and pour over boiling syrup.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, lemon rind and soda in mixer bowl; mix well.
Stir in margarine.
Reserve 1 cup flour mixture. Press remaining flour mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread cranberry sauce over baked layer. Sprinkle with
mixture of reserved flour mixture and pecans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Cool. Cut into bars.
May be frozen up to 12 months.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1/4-inch strips, cutting across the grain. Heat oil and add chicken until they go white (about 3 minutes). Add green pepper, onion, celery, water chestnuts, broth, salt and ginger.
Cover and cook about 6 minutes.
Mix soy sauce with cornstarch.
Add to skillet with bean sprouts.
Turn heat down and simmer few minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges; save juice.
Add enough water to make 1 cup. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Then add orange sections and chill until you are ready to serve, about 2 hours.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and drain beans; cover with water.
Add salt; soak overnight.
In morning drain beans and add 2 quarts water and ham hock with ham shreds.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 3 hours. Cut ham off bone; return meat to pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes more.
Enjoy!!

title: pig eat'in cake
directions: Put cake
mix,	eggs,
oil and oranges in bowl and mix. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate town chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour to mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by rounded spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sausage-bean stuffing supreme
directions: Combine 4 cups water, beans and chicken bouillon cubes.
Bring to boiling and boil gently for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add sausage, tomato, onion, celery, parsley, garlic, thyme, bay leaf and salt.
Return to boiling. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in wine.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes more or until liquid is absorbed. Makes 4 cups stuffing, enough for a 5 to 6 pound duckling.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured pan, 9 x 13-inch size.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Add sugar and shortening to boiling water.
Cool in mixing bowl.
Add yeast that has been mixed with lukewarm water.
Add cold water, eggs and salt.
Add flour 2 cups at a time.
Place dough in bowl and rub with vegetable oil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese cut outs
directions: Mix butter and cheese, then add soup mix and flour.
Blend and shape into ball and chill.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.
(If difficult to roll out, add more flour.)

title: cheer-up chicken soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine water and broth; bring to a boil. Meanwhile, cut chicken into 1/2-inch chunks.
Add to liquid with carrots, celery and potatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, onions and thyme.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Peel and coarsely grate cucumbers.
Wrap in a paper towel and squeeze gently to completely remove juice.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar. Fold in sour cream and chill mixture until thickened.
Fold in cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Pour into greased mold and chill until firm. Serves 6.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pans.
Stir ingredients in pan until moist.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: black forest cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake batter in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Remove cake layers from pans and cool on rack.
Place 1 cooled layer on serving plate.
Spread half can of cherries on first layer.
Top with second layer.
Combine sugar, vanilla, orange rind, and cream.
Whip cream mixture until cream holds its shape.
Spread on second layer and sides.
Spread half of cherries on top of whipped cream.
Sprinkle with chocolate shavings.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together in order listed.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is firm.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in large pan over low heat. After completely melted, pour box of cereal into pan and coat each piece. Be careful not to break up cereal. After coated, pour box of powdered sugar into trash bag, then pour cereal over it and shake bag until cereal is coated.

title: molded shrimp loaf
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Bring tomato soup to a boil in saucepan.
Add gelatin and allow to cool.
When cool, add cream cheese.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; cover and chill for 2 to 4 hours or until set. To serve, unmold on large platter.
Garnish with lettuce and lemon and lime slices.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the lemonade and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Cool in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Place apples in pie shell, then sprinkle with the sugar.
Mix together the flour, oleo, nutmeg and brown sugar and sprinkle over the top of the apples.
Bake at about 375° until apples are tender.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package lime jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Blend cream cheese to jello.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Pour milk over crackers.
When soft, add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 2 layers at 375° for 25 minutes.
Put together with whipped cream or topping.

title: chocolate snack cake(without eggs)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients (dry) in bowl with fork; stir in rest.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cake can be mixed in pan.
Recipe can be doubled and made in 13 x 9-inch pan, but should be mixed with mixer.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix and beat ingredients 5 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes in well-greased Bundt pan.
Can be made 2 days in advance.
Frost or glaze as preferred.

title: honey cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then eggs.
Add honey, sour milk and vanilla.
Beat well and add dry ingredients.
Chill and form into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mushrooms a la grecque
directions: Place tomatoes in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole and add wine. Cook over low heat 20 to 25 minutes.
Strain and discard liquid. Add the mushrooms (wash them first!), pepper, bay leaf and olive oil to tomato pulp.
Cook 30 minutes over low heat.
Correct seasoning with salt and pepper.
Serve cold.
Serves 4.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk and beat until smooth.
Dip franks in batter and fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
If batter is too thick add some more milk.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Dissolve raspberry sherbet in cranberry juice until slushy. Add the 7-Up.
Serves about 30.

title: creative noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook entire package of noodles.
Let sit in water for 1 hour or overnight.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix yolk mixture with drained noodles.
Add any optional ingredients.

title: sherrie broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
30 minutes.
Drain water.
Mix together cheese, egg, soup, mayonnaise and mushrooms.
Pour over cooked broccoli and stir well.
Cover with cracker crumbs and drizzle butter on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushrooms and sour cream.
Bake at 350° until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms and juice before serving.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate fudge deluxe
directions: In a 3 1/2-quart saucepan, mix sugar with dry gelatin.
Add milk, corn syrup, chocolate and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, to 238° on thermometer.
Remove from heat; pour into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool about 25 minutes or to 110°.
Beat with wooden spoon until candy thickens. Stir in walnuts.
Spread into prepared pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak and discard.
Press peppercorns into both sides of steak with heel of hand.
Melt butter in pan large enough to hold steak.
When butter is sizzling, brown steak on one side, turn and brown second side.
Reduce heat and finish cooking steak.
(To test, make a small slash with a sharp knife to see if steak is as done as you want it to be.)
Season with salt to taste.
Obviously, makes one serving.

title: chocolate carmelita bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine first seven ingredients; mix well.
Reserve one cup; press remaining on bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown; cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix chocolate pudding mix
according to instructions on the box.
In
a
13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish, tear up the angel food cake
into	small
(bite
size) pieces.
Spoon on pudding mixture and top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn and red pepper.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serve with cheese sprinkled over it, tortilla chips and sour cream, if desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, soda and salt.
Add oil and mix.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake slowly for 40 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a baking pan.
In a bowl beat butter until creamy.
Beat in 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and then work in 2 cups flour to make a smooth dough.
Press dough in an even layer in the prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes until slightly puffed.
Next, beat eggs in a bowl with a wire whisk.
Beat in granulated sugar, lemon peel and juice.
Sift remaining 1/4 cup flour over egg mixture and stir in.
Prick top of crust with a fork about an inch away from each other all over.
Pour egg mixture over crust and bake 30 minutes until egg mixture is set. Remove from oven.
Cool and sprinkle top with 1 1/2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat juice and dissolve jello.
Add water and cool until slightly thickened.
Stir in celery, onion and horseradish.
Add sliced stuffed olives and shrimp if you like variation.
Pour into ring mold or individual molds.

title: chocolate drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container with a lid. Shake until dry milk is dissolved. Drink immediately or chill in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil and add the peanuts. Stir constantly until peanuts are golden brown.
Remove from stove and add the soda.
Stir until foaming almost stops.
Pour on greased sheet pan.
Use heavy pan, use wooden spoon and make on a clear, cool day.

title: merry cherry salad
directions: Drain fruits and reserve juice.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add fruit juice.
Chill until partially congealed.
Blend cream cheese with lemon juice, salt and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream.
Beat chilled gelatin until light and fluffy.
Fold into cream cheese mixture and fruits.
Pour into chilled buttered pan.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let warm enough to cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with maraschino cherries or coconut.

title: rice balls
directions: Drain rice on cloth.
Add eggs, salt, pepper and parsley. Chill.
Fry in deep oil until light brown.

title: western style stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add beef; cook until no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to combine. Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until veggies are crisp-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy oven fries
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters lengthwise.
Mix with olive oil. Sprinkle with pepper, salt, garlic powder and cayenne pepper. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: martha washington chocolates
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into 1-inch balls. Chill for 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin. Using toothpicks, dip chilled balls into chocolate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Scrub fresh, crisp cucumbers.
Wash but don't peel.
Slice cucumbers crosswise and mix with onions and green peppers.
Mix the salt with the vegetables and bury 1-quart cracked ice in mixture. Cover with a heavy lid.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and prepare the following:
Blend sugar, turmeric and cloves together.
Add mustard and celery seed and vinegar.
If the vinegar is too strong, substitute 1 cup of water for 1 cup vinegar.
Pour this mixture over the vegetables in a large pan; heat to scalding, stirring occasionally but do not boil.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Let stand about 3 to 4 weeks before using.

title: garden vegetables with pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, adding broccoli to water last 2 minutes of cooking time; drain well.
Add process cheese spread and milk to pasta mixture in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until process cheese melts.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Mix the above ingredients except flour; sift in enough flour to make a stiff dough. Roll out and cut with a cookie cutter. Bake in a moderate oven until golden brown.

title: sugar free dream sicle fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add ice (to make 2 cups).
Stir until melted.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add pudding and oranges and mix with mixer.
Add cool whip and mix with mixer. Refrigerate.
Tastes great and it's quick!

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all together in a sauce pan. Cook on medium high until it thickens, stirring often.

title: ham 'n' cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form a ball and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Put drained beans and ham hock in large soup kettle.
Add water and salt; bring to boil.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes; add other ingredients.
Cook 2 hours or until beans are tender and liquid thick.
Serve over steamed rice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Sift together flour and sugar and add beer.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo.
Pour over top and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: molasses yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over rolled oats, molasses, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast, eggs and 3 cups flour to oat mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down. Shape into rolls and place in shallow pan.
Cover loosely.
Rise until doubled in size, 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Makes 3 dozen rolls. Enjoy!

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onion in enough water for simmering (about 1 1/2 cups) until tender.
Drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Return 1 cup liquid to squash.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Prepare potatoes, onions and celery.
Place in saucepan, add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and turn to high heat.
Bring to rolling boil, switch to simmer and cook for 20 minutes.
Then add milk and bring almost to a boil, again using high heat.
While this is heating, measure flour into bowl and add egg.
Stir with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in egg, flour mixture and butter.
Switch to simmer for at least 15 minutes.

title: wagon wheel vegetable platter
directions: Begin your platter with a bed of lettuce on a round platter. Add thick slices of tomatoes and thin slices of onion around edge of platter.
Place pieces of avocado on tomatoes.
Make spokes with raw cucumber sticks or celery sticks.
Fill center of dish with radish roses and carrot curls.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar real good.
Add eggs and flour alternately, adding flour first and last.
Cut fruit and nuts fine and mix with a little flour.
(This keeps all the fruit from going to the bottom of cake.)
Add vanilla.
Mix nuts and fruit with batter.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Rinse, drain and hull berries.
Add sugar and mash.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into refrigerator trays; freeze 2 to 3 hours. Remove from trays; break into chunks.
Beat with electric beater until smooth.
Refreeze until firm.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: texas pie
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients together until blended.
Stir in coconut and pineapple.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 5 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°; bake for about 1 hour longer.

title: lemon herb chicken with hollandaise sauce
directions: Dip chicken breasts in bread crumbs.
Place the fillets on microwavable dish and cover with a domed, microwavable cover.
Cook fillet on High for 4 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn and continue cooking on High for 4 additional minutes.
Add 1/8 cup of water to the frozen broccoli in microwavable dish and cover.
Microwave broccoli for 3 minutes on High.
Separate the broccoli and microwave for 3 additional minutes on High.
Divide broccoli and place each portion with a chicken breast.
Pour Hollandaise Sauce equally over both portions and serve.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Boil potatoes in skins just until tender.
Chill in refrigerator.
When chilled, grate potatoes.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, milk, margarine, 3/4 cup grated cheese, salt, pepper, onion and grated potatoes.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add flour, then cheese (cut up cheese into chunks, so it will melt quickly).
Then add mushrooms and soup.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add to mixture.
Heat the dip well, then pour into chafing dish and keep hot.
Serve with Fritos.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Mix melted butter with dry cake mix; set aside 1 1/2 cups. Press rest into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixed Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter on top.
Crumble rest of cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and cut.

title: jimmy dean's calico beans
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: clara's nesselrode pie
directions: In a small bowl, soak the gelatin in the cold water for about 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg yolks.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar and cream.

title: flying saucer cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients, then add the next 2.
Mix and add the next 4 ingredients and stir in the last 4 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix soup, mayo, milk and lemon juice.
Heat and stir.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, broccoli on bottom, some sauce, cut up chicken, remainder of sauce, grated cheese, bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: andy's country pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add chips and melt.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Bake in greased muffin pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cut up vegetables; grind in food chopper, using coarse blade. Add salt.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Rinse in cold water. Drain well.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into a ball.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart for crusty sides, touching for soft sides.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 1 dozen biscuits.

title: strawberry-banana freeze
directions: Reserve 4 berries for garnish.
Puree other berries and banana in blender.
Add jam and milk.
Blend.
Freeze.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat eggs in creamed mixture, one at a time.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add alternately the dry ingredients and sour cream to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Add boiling water and vanilla. Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check after 70 minutes with toothpick, ovens may vary.
Do not overbake.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: pink wedding punch
directions: Mix lemonade and ice water.
Add pineapple juice and Hawaiian Punch.
Stir thoroughly.
Add 7-Up.
Scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour punch over sherbet very slowly.
Punch will be very frothy.
Serves 100 four ounce servings.

title: mom's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix
eggs, oil and water.
Blend in cake mix and peanut butter.
Drop
by
teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Mash down with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and water and mix.
Shape into balls and freeze or roll out and use.
Makes about 7 crusts.
You may re-roll or re-shape; dough doesn't get tough!

title: cream of carrot soup with homemade croutons
directions: Melt butter in a pan and saute the onions, potatoes and carrots for ten minutes on med low heat.
Add stock and sugar and bring slowly to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
In a food processor, puree soup.
Return to pan and add half and half. Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: taco soup
directions: *Ground chicken or turkey may be used or 4 chicken breasts which have been boiled, deboned and cut up may be used.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook all ingredients, thicken to consistency you desire.
Top with biscuits.

title: pimento cheese salad ball
directions: Mix all until well blended. Roll in nuts and chill.

title: "muddy buddies"
directions: Melt butter, chips and peanut butter in microwave for about 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla until smooth.
Pour mixture over cereal. Put powdered sugar in a bag.
Shake Chex and sugar until well coated.
Spread onto wax paper to dry.

title: cabbage rolls or pigs in the blanket
directions: Cook cabbage 25 to 30 minutes.
Peel leaves. Combine hamburger, rice, onion soup mix, onion, egg and 1/2 can tomato soup.
Roll meat mixture up in cabbage leaves.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place cabbage rolls in a large pan and cover with remainder of tomato sauce and soup. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: crock-pot macaroni # 1
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain and put into crock-pot.
Add other ingredients in this order: oil, milk, butter, eggs and pepper.
Top with the grated cheese and cook for 4 hours on low.
Turn off after 4 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Chop onion, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Combine ingredients for dressing.
Pour over pasta, onion and cucumbers.
Add tomatoes last.
Refrigerate for several hours, overnight, if possible. Will serve at least 12.

title: cabbage-beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain off grease.
In mixing bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef mixture to this and toss to mix well.
Pour uncooked rice into a 3-quart casserole.
Pour cabbage and ground beef mixture over rice.
Pour beef broth and water over mixture.
Cover casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumber delight pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and set aside to cool.
Wash, peel and slice cucumbers rather thick. Place onion and garlic in jars.
Add cucumbers, filling jar to top. Fill jar with vinegar mixture; seal.
Refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
(Liquid makes about 3 quarts.)

title: meowser's pickled brussels
directions: Wash and trim sprouts.
Thoroughly wash four 1-pint canning jars and lids.
In each jar, place 1 garlic clove, 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1 teaspoon peppercorns and then fill with Brussels sprouts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate squares and 2 tablespoons of milk until almost melted, stirring 1/2 way through.
Stir until completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, milk and sugar until well mixed. Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Put mix in pie crust.
Freeze until firm (3 to 4 hours).
Garnish with chocolate curls or shavings.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: You will need wooden skewers.
Choose five of the fruits (grapes are a must) and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Put a piece of each fruit on a wooden skewer, alternating with grapes.
A strawberry on top always adds color.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: yummy butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter 9-inch square pan. Mix all ingredients together, combining them well. Spread mixture in pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until dry on top and almost firm to touch. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: working man's breakfast
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.
Brown onion in the bacon drippings.
Add bread, cheese and potato.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture.
Beat eggs; pour into mixture.
Season to taste and cook until set, stirring occasionally.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in margarine. Reserve 1 cup and press remaining onto bottom of pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown; cool 10 minutes.
Top with chocolate pieces.

title: deanna's apple crisp
directions: Wash, peel, core and slice apples.
Sprinkle lightly with hot water and a few drops lemon juice.
Also a few tablespoons of sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Arrange apple mixture in bottom of large greased baking pan.
In mixing bowl, add melted butter; keep adding remaining sugar and flour to form crumbly mixture, working with a fork.
Sprinkle butter-flour mixture evenly over sliced apples.
A few chopped walnuts, pecans or wheat germ give an added crunch to topping.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes or until apples are tender and crumb topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or softened vanilla ice cream.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook shrimp according to package directions.
Thaw crab meat. Cook rice according to package directions using seasoning in package.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: holiday cranberry muffins(heartwarming christmas 1991)
directions: Let cranberries stand overnight in 1/2 cup sugar.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients all at once.
Stir until moistened.
Add cranberries and stir.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Yields 18.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Assemble 3 lasagna strips into a buttered 9x12 inch baking dish.
Mix cheese into hot mashed potatoes.
Add 1/2 potato-cheese mixture.
Layer 3 more lasagna noodles and repeat with potato and cheese mixture.
Saute oleo and onions until golden.
Pour over casserole.
Bake 20 minutes a 350 degrees uncovered.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fresh apple pie(large recipe)
directions: Arrange apples in 8 deep pie pans that have been lined with pastry.
Mix the following and sprinkle over the apples: sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Cover with pastry.
Brush top with milk.
Bake approximately 15 minutes at 425°, then 30 minutes at 350° or until apples are done.
Yield:
8 (8-inch) pies.

title: taco snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine in a large bowl, tossing to coat well with seasoning.
Drizzle with melted margarine and toss to coat well.
Store in an airtight container. Makes an excellent anytime snack.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and onions in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of flat baking pan.
Lay washed chicken breasts on top of rice; sprinkle lemon pepper and salt on chicken and rice mixture.
Place onion slices on top of mixture and pour the water over rice.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well and return to the pan.
Add remaining ingredients, tossing lightly to coat the noodles.
Good with veal and poultry.
Serves 4.

title: san francisco chops
directions: Trim pork chops.
In a microsafe dish, combine the oil and garlic.
Spread evenly in dish.
Microwave at High power for 1 minute.
Combine sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar and pepper in bowl. Add pork chops to dish, turning to coat.
Pour sauce over chops. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High power for 4 minutes, turning chops and dish once after 2 minutes.
Keep covered. Microwave at Medium power for 12 to 15 minutes, until no pink remains.
Remove chops to serving dish.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir into pan juices.
Microwave at High power for 1 to 2 minutes, until thick.
Pour sauce over chops and serve.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine first three ingredients and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Do not boil.
Remove and add the remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Bottle to store.

title: black bean tortilla pinwheels
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream in bowl until blended.
Stir in Monterey Jack cheese, olives, onion, salt and garlic powder. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Place beans in food processor or blender; process until smooth.
Spread each tortilla with a thin layer of beans.
Spread thin layer of cream cheese mixture over beans.
Roll up tortillas lightly.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until chilled.
Cut 3/4-inch slices and serve with salsa.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour last and one package of Dream Whip.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan. Blend salt, pepper, crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip meat in eggs and then in crumbs twice. Place meat in buttered pan.
Cook 20 minutes in 400° oven; turn and bake 20 minutes on the other side.

title: strawberry supreme cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add strawberries.
Bake in greased and floured pan per directions on box.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Spray a 1-quart casserole dish with nonstick coating.
Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl except potatoes.
Gently stir in potatoes.
Spoon onto prepared baking dish.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake casserole 45 minutes or until slightly puffed and top is lightly browned.

title: california tamale pie
directions: In skillet or slow cooking pot with browning unit, cook meat until crumbly.
Drain.
In large bowl, mix cornmeal, milk and egg. Add meat, dry chili seasoning mix, seasoned salt, tomatoes, corn and olives.
Put in slow cooker or crock-pot and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook for another 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meal in a bowl soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook ground beef or ground pork and onion until meat is browned or onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in beef broth, water, peas, potatoes, mushrooms, carrots, sage, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 6.

title: monster cookies
directions: Melt margarine and cream with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, which have been beaten together.
Then beat in the dry ingredients with the mixture.
Add rest of the ingredients by hand.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Use an ice cream scoop or tablespoon to drop dough onto the cookie sheet.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Beat Egg Beaters and add remaining ingredients. Pour into a large cast-iron skillet already sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add egg, molasses, ginger and cinnamon. Sift the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add sifted dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with the cold water. Drop by spoonful (large) onto greased baking sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes in moderate hot 375° oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish. Pour in peaches and sprinkle cinnamon on peaches. Mix all other ingredients and pour on top of peaches. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: calico bean casserole #2
directions: Cook bacon, hamburger and onions in frypan. Add vinegar, brown sugar and mustard. Simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in the beans. Put meat mixture in bean pot or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350° or slow cooker on low for 4 hours.

title: graham cracker dream bars
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and egg.
Cook until it comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
On top of graham crackers, spread filling on graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top of filling.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add other ingredients, except shrimp and lemon; simmer 2 hours.
Add shrimp during the last 30 minutes and put in whole lemon the last 10 minutes.
Serve with rice and lemon juice.
Serves 6.

title: sue's rosh hashana chicken
directions: Place chicken in large Ziploc bag(s) with lemon juice. Marinate overnight, turning bags occasionally. Next day, pat dry chicken with paper towels. Dredge in seasoned flour. Fry in oil until golden. Drain on paper towel.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in sauce pan and stir until not grainy. Then boil until it forms a soft ball when dropped into ice water. Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Then add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat well.
Spread into 9 x 9 inch pan.

title: potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl. Add cold water. Let stand 30 minutes. Dry potatoes. Spray pan with nonstick spray. Place potatoes in pan. Spray potatoes with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt. Bake for 20 minutes at 425°. Using spatula, turn potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic. Bake until golden potatoes.

title: great caesar's roast
directions: Partially crush one cup Caesar Croutons.
Add one Tbsp. each chopped chives and parmesan cheese and two Tbsp. melted butter. Cut three medium tomatoes in half (cross-wise).
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with croutons mixture.
Broil until brown.
Serve with roast.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine Bisquick and onions.
Combine 2 beaten eggs and milk, then add to Bisquick mixture.
Stir only until the mixture is moistened.

title: rice pudding(rizogalo)
directions: Heat milk and water in saucepan.
Add rice; stir.
Add sugar, salt and butter and stir, then let simmer for 50 minutes.
Beat 2 eggs in separate bowl and slowly add hot mixture.
Beat constantly.
Add vanilla and stir gently.
Ladle into dessert dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: szechuan steak
directions: Mix all the ingredients except steak in a 10 x 13-inch dish. Score steak on both sides.
Marinate for several hours.
Grill.

title: chicken parmesan(aunt sue's recipe)
directions: Dip chicken in eggs. Roll in bread crumbs. Brown in olive oil and garlic (both sides). Grease casserole.
On bottom, layer spaghetti sauce, chicken, Mozzarella cheese, garlic, oregano and Parmesan.
Layer more spaghetti sauce and top with more Parmesan.

title: peanut butter chocolate centered cookies
directions: Mix first six ingredients together until fluffy.
Separately mix the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Then add these to the first six ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into 1 inch balls and roll each ball in sugar.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 - 11 minutes, remove quickly from oven.
Place one chocolate candy kiss into the center of each cookie pointed side down.
Bake for exactly one minute longer.
Remove from oven and immediately spread chocolate over each cookie.
You may want to leave the cookie as is or you may place a butterscotch chip in each one.
Freezes well.
Makes 6 - 7 dozen cookies.

title: rum sauce
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually, then rum flavoring very slowly. Add well beaten egg yolks and milk or cream. Cook over hot water until it thickens as a custard. Pour onto beaten egg whites. It is delicious on bread pudding.

title: fresh corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a casserole dish.
Put casserole dish in a pan of water and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mozzarella casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain off any excess grease.
Combine with remaining ingredients (except Mozzarella) and place in 3-quart casserole dish. Top with Mozzarella and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: greek salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Add garlic and cook until done, but still firm.
Drain.
Add chopped onion.
Cool to warm.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
